# Whale Tracker — environment variables
#
# This is a static HTML template. No server-side env vars are required
# to run the demo. Variables below are documented for production integrations.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   Fill in the values for whichever data provider you connect.
#   Never commit .env to version control.

# ── Data Provider (choose one or build a custom adapter) ──────────────────────

# Etherscan / Etherscan-compatible
# ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=your_etherscan_api_key_here

# Bitquery (GraphQL multi-chain indexer)
# BITQUERY_API_KEY=your_bitquery_api_key_here

# Nansen / Arkham / Dune (commercial whale intelligence APIs)
# NANSEN_API_KEY=your_nansen_api_key_here

# WebSocket endpoint for real-time tx streaming
# WS_PROVIDER_URL=wss://your-ws-endpoint

# ── Optional: backend proxy ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If you proxy API calls through your own server to protect keys:
# API_BASE_URL=https://your-proxy.example.com/api

# ── Optional: alert integrations ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id
# DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/...
